HEADWORD: Geothermometer
<hw>Ge`o*ther*mom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>ge`a</grk>, <grk>gh^</grk>, the earth + E.
<ets>thermometer</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>A thermometer
specially constructed for measuring temperatures at a depth below the
surface of the ground.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

